Interface AccessListener

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    AutomaticAccessListener

    public interface AccessListener
    An interface for implementing handlers on access requests

      Callback that is called when an access request has completed succesfully with a result

    • Method Detail

      • onAccessStarted

        void onAccessStarted(Reader reader)
        Callback that is called when an access request is about to start. This is the app's opportunity to give some feedback about the process starting.
        Parameters:
        reader - The reader that is having an access request started

      • onAccessCompleted

        void onAccessCompleted(Reader reader,
                       AccessResult accessResult,
                       ReaderConnectionError error)
        Callback that is called when an access request has completed succesfully with a result
        Parameters:
        reader - The reader that an access decision was made on
        accessResult - If non-null, the access request completed, and this contains the decision that was made for the access request
        error - If non-null, the access request failed, and this contains the error
